Replace null values in a numerical column with the mean or median of the non-null values in that column. This approach can help maintain the statistical properties of the data.

For categorical data, you can replace null values with the mode value in that column.

Age - numerical column

Embarked - categorical data

Since the missing values in cabin column is greater we can drop that specific column

Handling Outliers

In [25]:
median_fare = df['Fare'].median()

upper_bound = df['Fare'].quantile(0.8)

df['Fare'] = df['Fare'].clip(upper=upper_bound).fillna(median_fare)
In [26]:
sns.boxplot(df['Fare'])
Out[26]:
<Axes: >
In [27]:
median_fare = df['Age'].median()

upper_bound = df['Age'].quantile(0.8)

df['Age'] = df['Age'].clip(upper=upper_bound).fillna(median_fare)
